ass ability Pet Hold.....</span><hr size=1> Hmmm, was I the only one who saw Shadowcross's reply? Must be a EZboard bug. /shrug<br><br>/chuckle<br><br>Guys, would this topic not be better discussed on one of the pet class specfic boards? Necro? Mage?<br><br>You would get a lot more feedback, and maybe just maybe they already have a rabid discussion going on already. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urulan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rulan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www3.sympatico.ca/headleya/rulan_icon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 12:08:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/headleya/rulan_60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wanted opinion of the Class ability Pet Hold.....</span><hr size=1> http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower <p><h6><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55098>Rulan Jiggamental</a><BR>Arch Mage of <a href=http://www.warzonedirect.com/DO/MainDO.html>Veneration</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 12:50:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wanted opinion of the Class ability Pet Hold.....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Hmmm, was I the only one who saw Shadowcross's reply? Must be a EZboard bug. /shrug<br><br>/chuckle<br><br>Guys, would this topic not be better discussed on one of the pet class specfic boards? Necro? Mage?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Are you encouraging willfull ignorance?  Sure, a question about magicians will probably get the most knowledgeable response on a magician board, however, objecting to a topic just because it would really be a bit better someplace else is stupid, in my opinion.  I post a great deal at the Magicians Tower and would welcome educated discussion on topics relating to rogues.  We all play the same game, and honestly, I have found that many people tend to prefer melee classes into groups simply because they do not fully understand how other casters work, and I think continuing to promote such ignorance does a disservice to everyone.<br><br>Cosider, for example, this reply:<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It's the fact that pets have no resists, and don't last long against anything thath has a AE damage spell.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I can now take this opportunity to clarify this inaccurate statement.<br><br>Pets, specifically magician pets, do indeed have strong resistances, but only to one element.  These resists are insanely high, to the point of being immune to all but the most powerful of attacks.  Lord Rak'Ashiir in CoM, for example, has almost zero chance of hitting a mage fire pet with his AE, though Gorenaire can probably deal damage to an Air pet, though not very well.  To summarize the resistances for each pet:<br><br>Earth:  Disease<br>Fire:  Fire<br>Air:  Cold<br>Water:  Poison<br>Dyzil pet:  Fire<br>Epic pet:  none, though apparently better general resistances all around.<br><br>The problem with ToV is the alternation of Fire and Cold based AEs.  You would be replacing pets every few pulls, which would be a royal pain in the ass.  Unless you absolutely need the damage from the pet, it's not really worth the hassle and the pathing risks.<br><br>Though I do not yet have the skill, I do believe /pet hold would be suffecient for a fairly attentive magician to be able to keep his pet from getting aggroed by overlapping AE's. <p><font face = "Arial" color=0000EE><center><b>Goladus Mistrydia</b></font><br><font face = "Arial" color=0000EE>56th Conjurer |  <a href = "http://www.darkblood.com">Darkblood</a> |<a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8506">Profile</a> | Solusek Ro</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:14:27 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~shadowcross/clip.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wanted opinion of the Class ability Pet Hold.....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I post a great deal at the Magicians Tower and would welcome educated discussion on topics relating to rogues.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>That sir, is your humble opinion. I am not going to rate it in any way.<br><br>BUT...<br><br>Many rogues that frequent this board would NOT welcome educated discussion on topics relating to casters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span